pages.text:
FL's Oldest Microbrewery • Pub Food • Live Music
Founded in 1996. Dunedin Brewery has positioned itself as an originator in the Florida craft beer scene; is Downtown Dunedin's go-to spot for comfort food; & houses an intimate yet nationally renowned music venue.
Fresh ideas go on tap weekly. Food Creations drop every Tuesday while new beers and elixirs are guaranteed on Friday. Live music is the soul of our operation with (both local & touring) bands performing in Downtown every weekend on one of our two stages and a weekly
Wednesday Night Open Jam
.
Our goal is to create a space in Dunedin where you can let your shoulders relax with those you love in confidence that the beer,
food
, & music you experience is not only top notch but creative, fresh, & original.
We are often imitated, but never truly replicated. Come see why. Cheers & Sláinte!

Florida's Oldest Craft Brewery
The Original, Brewing since 1996
We weren't the first to make beer in Florida, but we're the oldest distributing microbrewery still in operation. Come taste not only a bit of Florida history but the best beer in Downtown Dunedin.
Choose from a wide selection of ales & lagers, from our 3 most popular (Apricot Peach Ale, American Classic IPA, or Air) to one-offs by our brewmasters.
We also sell our beer to-go in 4-packs or 32oz Crowlers.
Best Bar Food in Dunedin
Welcome to our snug little Pub
Whether you're hungry for crunchy tacos, juicy
smashburgers
, or the best fried
chicken wings
in Dunedin, we've got you covered. Bar food is our specialty, and we've taken it up a notch with nearly everything made fresh in house.
Pair your favorite local IPA with our locally famous sauces like Snakebite or Florida Heat hot sauce.
When you're in Downtown Dunedin, it's hard to pass up a fresh taste of history with our signature Florida eats (especially during
Happy Hour
).
Late Night Chicken Wings til 11pm on Friday & Saturday!
More than just a Music Venue
We encourage original art & musical performance
From Colonel Bruce to Joe Marcinek. Rage Tributes to save the neighborhood. Music is at the heart of what we do. Countless bands have graced our stage, numerous were founded there. From Grammy award winners, national & regional touring acts, to local Dunedin songwriters, featuring every genre, we strive to create a place where artists feel ready to create freely in front of a gathering of engaged listeners.
Our musical program is synonymous with our musical community. It also pairs well with all of our handcrafted beer and food.
We have two stages, our historical Pub Stage and our latest expansion, the
Moon Tower
.
